1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,680
THIS DRAMA IS CREATED
FOR ENTERTAINMENT PURPOSES

2
00:00:04,760 --> 00:00:07,680
ALL CHARACTERS, SETTINGS
AND EVENTS ARE ENTIRELY FICTITIOUS

3
00:00:07,760 --> 00:00:10,920
THERE IS NO INTENT TO REFERENCE
ANY ORGANIZATIONS OR INDIVIDUALS

4
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:11,840
<i>So Dad sent you?</i>

5
00:03:13,200 --> 00:03:15,080
Yes. He wanted to know whether you still

6
00:03:15,160 --> 00:03:17,800
serve the country or became a mole…

7
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:21,400
A mole? Me?

8
00:03:21,480 --> 00:03:23,080
Hey, you mole!

9
00:03:24,880 --> 00:03:26,800
<i>It wasn't easy for me to get close enough</i>

10
00:03:26,880 --> 00:03:28,760
<i>for them to trust me, Dad.</i>

11
00:03:28,840 --> 00:03:33,560
Right now, they're the only option
to keep this mission going.

12
00:03:33,640 --> 00:03:36,560
Everyone entering Pha Mok now

13
00:03:36,640 --> 00:03:38,240
is locked into the screening system.

14
00:03:39,240 --> 00:03:41,760
<i>If someone who isn't an insider</i>
<i>like me changes the data,</i>

15
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:42,960
<i>within two days</i>

16
00:03:43,480 --> 00:03:45,560
<i>they'll know exactly</i>
<i>who the seven of you are.</i>

17
00:03:47,200 --> 00:03:48,040
Done.

18
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:01,320
Where is the agent data?

19
00:04:39,040 --> 00:04:41,200
- Hey! Where's the fire?
- Hey. Hurry up.

20
00:04:41,280 --> 00:04:42,400
- Fire.
- Huh?

21
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:16,080
Quiet.

22
00:05:24,080 --> 00:05:25,040
Where is she?

23
00:05:36,200 --> 00:05:37,360
What's up?

24
00:05:38,280 --> 00:05:39,960
Nothing suspicious?

25
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:43,800
Suddenly there's not a damn thing at all?

26
00:05:44,360 --> 00:05:45,440
How is that possible?

27
00:05:57,920 --> 00:05:59,080
See?

28
00:05:59,160 --> 00:06:02,360
If I hadn't helped you, you'd have been
caught back in the server room.

29
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:09,640
What are you doing? I came to help.
Why are you pointing a gun at me?

30
00:06:09,720 --> 00:06:11,480
You're done. Get off me.

31
00:06:12,360 --> 00:06:14,520
- You're heavy.
- Well.

32
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:17,120
Are you blushing? Acting all jumpy.

33
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:18,760
You know "In-car"?

34
00:06:18,840 --> 00:06:21,240
The back seat's this wide, real comfy.

35
00:06:21,320 --> 00:06:23,400
Are you messing with me, you pervert?

36
00:06:23,480 --> 00:06:25,800
I'll stop. Sorry, sorry.

37
00:06:25,880 --> 00:06:29,280
I'll stop. Let go. Get your foot off.

38
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:30,960
You deserve this.

39
00:06:31,040 --> 00:06:32,800
Please. That's enough.

40
00:06:32,880 --> 00:06:34,280
- You pervert!
- No…

41
00:06:35,520 --> 00:06:36,640
Wait. Hold on!

42
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:38,520
- I can't take it anymore.
- Hey, calm down.

43
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:39,680
- You even know how to massage?
- Hey.

44
00:06:39,760 --> 00:06:41,200
Calm down. What did I do wrong?

45
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:44,160
Calm down. I gave you a massage, didn't I?

46
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:45,160
Firm pressure, right?

47
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:46,440
But it hurt, you know?

48
00:06:46,520 --> 00:06:48,080
- I didn't mean to.
- Excuse me.

49
00:06:59,680 --> 00:07:01,040
We sincerely apologize.

50
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:03,000
If our service wasn't satisfactory,

51
00:07:03,080 --> 00:07:05,600
may we offer additional service,

52
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:07,680
or another free massage session?

53
00:07:09,920 --> 00:07:11,160
Please, sir.

54
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:15,760
Fine, but make this guy
go retrain his massage skills.

55
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:27,680
He's all talk, huh?

56
00:07:28,280 --> 00:07:30,040
I should've taught him Muay Thai instead.

57
00:07:30,120 --> 00:07:31,720
- Walking away already?
- Mr. Songdej.

58
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:34,160
You're not that tough.
I'll knock you out like this.

59
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:35,080
- Ugh.
- Mr. Songdej.

60
00:07:35,680 --> 00:07:36,960
Wat Pho-certified?

61
00:07:37,680 --> 00:07:39,240
Dozens of certificates,

62
00:07:39,320 --> 00:07:41,840
years of overseas experience too?

63
00:07:41,920 --> 00:07:43,240
You faked your resume, right?

64
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:47,640
I'm not feeling well today.

65
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:51,040
So I didn't do well.
But I didn't want to take leave.

66
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:52,280
It'd affect my record.

67
00:07:53,200 --> 00:07:54,640
Don't worry about your record.

68
00:07:54,720 --> 00:07:56,080
If you work like this,

69
00:07:56,640 --> 00:07:58,320
then pack up, go home, take medicine,

70
00:07:58,400 --> 00:07:59,880
and don't come back here again.

71
00:07:59,960 --> 00:08:00,960
Huh?

72
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:03,840
You're firing me? Isn't that too much?

73
00:08:05,120 --> 00:08:06,520
What the hell are you doing, bro?

74
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:08,960
Only a few hours undercover
and you're fired already?

75
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:12,240
I was smooth as hell, but that manager

76
00:08:12,320 --> 00:08:13,880
isn't as kind as she looks to be.

77
00:08:19,960 --> 00:08:22,960
Ms. Khemjira, please have some sympathy
for working people like us.

78
00:08:24,160 --> 00:08:25,400
I feel sorry for him.

79
00:08:26,960 --> 00:08:27,880
You know each other?

80
00:08:29,240 --> 00:08:31,600
- No.
- I never met him before.

81
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:32,760
Khim.

82
00:08:40,240 --> 00:08:41,080
What's going on?

83
00:08:49,640 --> 00:08:53,200
Recently, Mr. Natee ordered
tighter control on everyone here.

84
00:08:53,880 --> 00:08:55,800
I'll report directly to Mr. Natee.

85
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:57,560
So he can check quickly.

86
00:09:01,400 --> 00:09:02,480
So?

87
00:09:02,560 --> 00:09:04,160
We don't know each other.

88
00:09:04,240 --> 00:09:06,760
I'll drag him out of here right now.

89
00:09:06,840 --> 00:09:08,520
- Go, go.
- Oh.

90
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:10,040
Yeah, I'll go.

91
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:17,360
All right, all right.

92
00:09:18,280 --> 00:09:20,200
Well? Total disaster.

93
00:09:20,280 --> 00:09:22,120
Even the gods can't help you now.

94
00:09:23,840 --> 00:09:25,040
I believe you now.

95
00:09:26,240 --> 00:09:27,560
Money really can do anything.

96
00:09:27,640 --> 00:09:29,400
Someone beautiful like an angel

97
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:31,560
turns out to be a criminal.

98
00:09:31,640 --> 00:09:33,560
Complaining won't help.

99
00:09:34,440 --> 00:09:35,720
If Sarge finds out,

100
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:37,760
we're dead for sure.

101
00:09:38,360 --> 00:09:40,400
Yeah, yeah. I'll figure something out.

102
00:09:41,320 --> 00:09:44,160
You've been marked by them.
I'll handle it.

103
00:09:57,040 --> 00:09:57,880
Damn it.

104
00:09:58,400 --> 00:10:00,080
This is what you called

105
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:02,360
"handled properly"?

106
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:03,280
Huh.

107
00:10:03,800 --> 00:10:04,640
Look.

108
00:10:08,720 --> 00:10:09,840
Here.

109
00:10:09,920 --> 00:10:11,240
What do you think?

110
00:10:11,320 --> 00:10:13,000
Dead quiet.

111
00:10:13,080 --> 00:10:14,560
Of course she is. She's unconscious.

112
00:10:15,160 --> 00:10:16,000
Ugh.

113
00:10:16,080 --> 00:10:17,720
Instead of just suspecting me,

114
00:10:17,800 --> 00:10:19,560
now they suspect both of us.

115
00:10:23,400 --> 00:10:24,920
A manager-level card.

116
00:10:25,640 --> 00:10:28,400
She should have the keys
all the way to central operations

117
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:30,000
that we suspect.

118
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:32,120
Let's… Hey.

119
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:35,320
It was me who started it,
so I have to end it too.

120
00:10:35,960 --> 00:10:37,240
Hang on a sec.

121
00:10:41,920 --> 00:10:43,920
Here it is.

122
00:10:46,440 --> 00:10:47,360
Give it to me.

123
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:49,080
I'll do it.

124
00:10:49,680 --> 00:10:53,240
Between a sniper like me
and a bomb disposal guy like you,

125
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:54,680
who's better at going undercover?

126
00:10:56,480 --> 00:10:57,560
And you,

127
00:10:58,480 --> 00:10:59,880
clean this up properly.

128
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:01,800
Damn.

129
00:11:01,880 --> 00:11:04,680
If those hands are so fast,
go pickpocket around Silom.

130
00:11:08,120 --> 00:11:09,760
Dead quiet, right?

131
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:35,600
Where's my friend?

132
00:11:39,560 --> 00:11:40,920
Still not answering? Say it.

133
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:42,120
Where is she?

134
00:11:46,760 --> 00:11:48,000
Where is my friend?

135
00:11:48,880 --> 00:11:49,960
Not yet.

136
00:12:05,720 --> 00:12:07,040
What's taking so long, bro?

137
00:12:11,680 --> 00:12:12,520
Huh?

138
00:12:14,960 --> 00:12:16,200
She was sitting right here.

139
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:20,760
She was sitting like this,
tied like this, or like this?

140
00:12:25,520 --> 00:12:26,840
What did you say? Say it again.

141
00:12:26,920 --> 00:12:29,440
- Quiet.
- Quiet, right?

142
00:12:29,520 --> 00:12:32,000
Dead quiet, huh?

143
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:33,080
Do you know

144
00:12:33,160 --> 00:12:34,520
- that hurt like hell.
- Napa.

145
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:36,160
- Stop, Napa.
- Ugh.

146
00:12:36,240 --> 00:12:38,480
- Stop. He's not one of them.
- You…

147
00:12:41,760 --> 00:12:43,560
- Not one of them?
- Yeah.

148
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:45,640
So who are they?

149
00:13:01,280 --> 00:13:02,440
I'm getting dizzy.

150
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:08,120
Finally.

151
00:13:08,960 --> 00:13:10,000
How's the plan going?

152
00:13:11,360 --> 00:13:12,440
The infiltration worked.

153
00:13:12,960 --> 00:13:15,680
In just a few hours,
we got insider-level intel.

154
00:13:16,440 --> 00:13:20,520
Your team's undercover skills are no joke.

155
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:21,720
- Of course.
- Right?

156
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:23,840
I told you our Seven Legends

157
00:13:23,920 --> 00:13:25,120
aren't amateurs.

158
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:27,120
- So how good are they?
- Exactly, Sarge.

159
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:28,080
Just look at the leader.

160
00:13:28,160 --> 00:13:30,000
Wow.

161
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:31,880
So how did you get this information?

162
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:33,760
Well…

163
00:13:33,840 --> 00:13:35,680
It wasn't that complicated.

164
00:13:35,760 --> 00:13:37,360
We got close to people on the inside.

165
00:13:38,360 --> 00:13:40,920
You might not believe this.

166
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:42,960
Do you believe in sacred things?

167
00:13:43,040 --> 00:13:44,360
- Oh, Buddha amulet.
- Whoa!

168
00:13:44,440 --> 00:13:46,480
- Go on, tell her.
- Ms. Duangnet, do you know Luang Pu Khem?

169
00:13:46,560 --> 00:13:48,480
- Yeah.
- This is Luang Pu Priao.

170
00:13:48,560 --> 00:13:50,680
The monk who walked
on fire path, 600 meters long.

171
00:13:50,760 --> 00:13:53,200
First step, nothing happened.
Next step, the robe started burning.

172
00:13:53,280 --> 00:13:54,440
- Oh.
- Third step, believe it or not?

173
00:13:54,520 --> 00:13:56,600
- What happened?
- Not funny.

174
00:13:57,320 --> 00:13:58,280
Not funny?

175
00:13:59,400 --> 00:14:02,680
I lost fellow agents,
better than all of you,

176
00:14:02,760 --> 00:14:04,880
because of mistakes and secrecy.

177
00:14:06,720 --> 00:14:08,880
Right now, we can't trust anyone.

178
00:14:08,960 --> 00:14:10,960
If anyone else finds out who we are,

179
00:14:12,160 --> 00:14:13,480
it means we're all dead.

180
00:14:16,880 --> 00:14:19,280
Come on, sometimes the job requires risks.

181
00:14:19,360 --> 00:14:20,480
- Don't nitpick.
- Yeah.

182
00:14:20,560 --> 00:14:21,960
- You're being overly cautious.
- Exactly.

183
00:14:22,040 --> 00:14:23,680
Trust my team.

184
00:14:25,600 --> 00:14:30,440
I guarantee these guys
don't screw up easily. Right?

185
00:14:30,520 --> 00:14:31,840
- Yes, Sarge.
- Yes, sir.

186
00:14:31,920 --> 00:14:34,520
A secret stays a secret.

187
00:14:35,920 --> 00:14:36,760
Okay?

188
00:14:39,840 --> 00:14:41,800
Good. Nodding means okay.

189
00:14:41,880 --> 00:14:43,680
- Yeah.
- Then let's get ready

190
00:14:43,760 --> 00:14:46,160
to wipe out their human-trafficking
network completely!

191
00:14:47,160 --> 00:14:48,280
- Yes, sir.
- Yeah.

192
00:14:48,360 --> 00:14:49,440
- Yeah.
- Yes, sir.

193
00:14:49,520 --> 00:14:51,240
- Yes, sir.
- Got it.

194
00:14:51,320 --> 00:14:54,200
When Ms. Duangnet speaks,
you all respond in perfect unison.

195
00:14:54,280 --> 00:14:56,360
- Oh?
- But when I say it,

196
00:14:56,440 --> 00:14:57,600
you all don't?

197
00:14:57,680 --> 00:14:59,000
Different people, Sarge.

198
00:14:59,080 --> 00:15:00,920
Again! Understood?

199
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:02,080
- Yes, sir!
- Yes.

200
00:15:02,160 --> 00:15:03,360
Still not perfect.

201
00:15:03,440 --> 00:15:04,720
Everyone. Understood?

202
00:15:04,800 --> 00:15:06,160
- Yes, ma'am!
- Yes, ma'am!

203
00:15:10,440 --> 00:15:11,280
Wait.

204
00:15:11,360 --> 00:15:13,760
One, two, three, four, five, six.

205
00:15:16,800 --> 00:15:17,640
Where's Dan?

206
00:15:17,720 --> 00:15:20,160
I sent him on a special mission.

207
00:15:20,240 --> 00:15:22,400
What special mission? Why wasn't I told?

208
00:15:33,680 --> 00:15:35,640
CONSTRUCTION SITE
LOWER YOUR SPEED

209
00:15:53,480 --> 00:15:54,480
Hey!

210
00:15:56,040 --> 00:15:57,600
Hey. Hey.

211
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:00,040
Hey.

212
00:16:26,360 --> 00:16:28,280
Damn. What the hell?

213
00:16:40,800 --> 00:16:42,560
No way there's nothing.

214
00:16:43,640 --> 00:16:45,280
Don't let me find out.

215
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:47,920
If you really are a mole like I suspect,

216
00:16:48,440 --> 00:16:49,400
you're dead.

217
00:16:55,320 --> 00:16:57,320
See? I knew it.

218
00:16:57,840 --> 00:16:59,400
He really does suspect you.

219
00:17:04,440 --> 00:17:07,119
I'm not stupid enough
to leave evidence tying back to me.

220
00:17:07,200 --> 00:17:10,119
But if Tiangmon's right-hand man
suspects you this much,

221
00:17:10,640 --> 00:17:11,599
it won't be long.

222
00:17:13,319 --> 00:17:14,560
Tiangmon doesn't know yet.

223
00:17:15,160 --> 00:17:17,240
I'm someone he deeply trusts.

224
00:17:18,119 --> 00:17:20,280
If the proof isn't solid enough,

225
00:17:20,359 --> 00:17:22,400
Jack won't risk upsetting Tiangmon.

226
00:17:24,079 --> 00:17:25,880
But if he's this suspicious,

227
00:17:27,119 --> 00:17:28,240
I think…

228
00:17:29,280 --> 00:17:30,320
Wait.

229
00:17:33,280 --> 00:17:35,600
Don't act alone under any circumstances.

230
00:17:37,320 --> 00:17:40,520
You can't afford the risk. If you fail,

231
00:17:41,280 --> 00:17:43,000
all our lives are on the line.

232
00:17:57,600 --> 00:17:59,200
What a relief.

233
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:02,720
Blood tests and X-rays showed
there's nothing to worry about.

234
00:18:03,960 --> 00:18:06,800
The doctor even said
you're in excellent shape.

235
00:18:06,880 --> 00:18:08,520
You may not need a long recovery.

236
00:18:09,720 --> 00:18:11,760
It still hurts, though.

237
00:18:11,840 --> 00:18:14,280
My arm might be broken.

238
00:18:14,360 --> 00:18:16,840
If it's broken, I'm screwed.

239
00:18:18,720 --> 00:18:20,560
I'm so sorry.

240
00:18:20,640 --> 00:18:23,600
It was my fault.
I wasn't watching the road.

241
00:18:23,680 --> 00:18:26,760
Actually, I wanted
to talk to you about that.

242
00:18:26,840 --> 00:18:28,880
The accident.

243
00:18:28,960 --> 00:18:30,760
I don't think it was a coincidence.

244
00:18:32,080 --> 00:18:33,960
I think it was…

245
00:18:35,800 --> 00:18:37,120
destiny.

246
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:39,240
Ugh.

247
00:18:39,320 --> 00:18:41,200
I was listening so seriously.

248
00:18:43,920 --> 00:18:47,000
Let's say from now on,
you don't owe me anything.

249
00:18:47,080 --> 00:18:48,440
I'll take care of myself.

250
00:18:48,520 --> 00:18:51,560
And I won't ask you for a single <i>baht.</i>

251
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:04,200
I think

252
00:19:05,120 --> 00:19:08,000
I can't just leave you alone.

253
00:19:08,080 --> 00:19:09,640
Then,

254
00:19:09,720 --> 00:19:13,040
I'll hire a private nurse to
take care of you until you're discharged.

255
00:19:15,600 --> 00:19:18,080
Thank you so much.
You're beautiful and kind.

256
00:19:18,160 --> 00:19:21,680
Then, do you mind if I ask your name?

257
00:19:22,520 --> 00:19:24,200
- My name is…
- Mook.

258
00:19:26,520 --> 00:19:27,720
Dad?

259
00:19:33,960 --> 00:19:36,440
<i>Tiangmon, a retired soldier.</i>

260
00:19:36,520 --> 00:19:38,200
Phoenix's right-hand man,

261
00:19:38,280 --> 00:19:40,480
the most powerful man in Pha Mok.

262
00:19:41,160 --> 00:19:43,600
So that means this guy's a big shot.

263
00:19:46,080 --> 00:19:47,360
An accident?

264
00:19:49,680 --> 00:19:51,280
Yes, sir. An accident.

265
00:19:52,600 --> 00:19:53,720
Hello, Dad.

266
00:19:53,800 --> 00:19:55,560
I'm not your dad. Don't call me that.

267
00:19:55,640 --> 00:19:56,840
Know your place.

268
00:19:56,920 --> 00:19:58,480
- Dad.
- Come here.

269
00:20:04,480 --> 00:20:07,200
What were you doing out so late, huh?

270
00:20:11,520 --> 00:20:13,560
What? Answer when I ask.

271
00:20:15,960 --> 00:20:18,000
I was looking for my cat.

272
00:20:18,520 --> 00:20:20,960
It ran away from home, and…

273
00:20:21,040 --> 00:20:22,840
I've been searching for days.

274
00:20:25,280 --> 00:20:27,720
- Your cat ran away?
- Yes, sir. My cat's missing.

275
00:20:27,800 --> 00:20:30,080
Very funny.
You think I'd believe that crap?

276
00:20:30,840 --> 00:20:32,880
Spill it.
What were you really doing there?

277
00:20:33,680 --> 00:20:35,040
- Answer me.
- Dad!

278
00:20:35,880 --> 00:20:37,200
Stop doing this, please.

279
00:20:37,280 --> 00:20:38,760
Ouch.

280
00:20:57,280 --> 00:20:58,800
Damn it.

281
00:20:59,320 --> 00:21:00,880
She was out all night.

282
00:21:01,560 --> 00:21:02,680
That's suspicious as hell.

283
00:21:09,600 --> 00:21:10,600
Are you looking for me?

284
00:21:10,680 --> 00:21:11,720
Duangnet.

285
00:21:12,680 --> 00:21:14,240
Hey! What?

286
00:21:18,800 --> 00:21:19,800
Ow! What the hell?

287
00:21:22,040 --> 00:21:22,920
Hey.

288
00:21:25,160 --> 00:21:26,320
Damn it.

289
00:21:29,920 --> 00:21:31,040
Damn it.

290
00:21:59,120 --> 00:22:00,400
Duangnet.

291
00:22:03,400 --> 00:22:05,040
You're not getting away today.

292
00:22:05,920 --> 00:22:06,960
You think you can escape?

293
00:22:07,560 --> 00:22:09,240
Duangnet!

294
00:22:13,280 --> 00:22:14,600
You're so tough, huh?

295
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:03,960
Hello, welcome…

296
00:23:06,720 --> 00:23:08,080
Juk sent me.

297
00:23:11,120 --> 00:23:12,000
Here you go.

298
00:23:13,600 --> 00:23:14,840
Is he

299
00:23:15,480 --> 00:23:17,480
the special guest you mentioned, Napa?

300
00:23:18,360 --> 00:23:19,240
Mr. Natee.

301
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:22,480
Yes. This is Mr. Hasus.

302
00:23:25,160 --> 00:23:26,880
Actually, my name is Hazus.

303
00:23:26,960 --> 00:23:29,200
But I like it
when Thai people call me that.

304
00:23:29,280 --> 00:23:30,520
It feels friendlier.

305
00:23:31,120 --> 00:23:34,640
And the reason I can speak Thai
is because I like Thai women.

306
00:23:34,720 --> 00:23:37,800
I like going to Patpong,
Pattaya, Phang Nga, Phuket,

307
00:23:37,880 --> 00:23:39,000
and

308
00:23:39,080 --> 00:23:41,000
I like doing business with Thai people.

309
00:23:42,880 --> 00:23:46,160
I hope this trip
will be a memorable one for you.

310
00:23:46,840 --> 00:23:48,720
Napa, take good care of Mr. Hasus,

311
00:23:49,720 --> 00:23:50,560
I mean Mr. Hazus.

312
00:23:51,280 --> 00:23:52,120
Yes.

313
00:23:52,800 --> 00:23:54,120
All right.

314
00:23:54,200 --> 00:23:55,680
Oh, wait, wait.

315
00:23:55,760 --> 00:23:57,000
- Hey!
- Hey!

316
00:23:57,080 --> 00:23:57,840
- Hey!
- Hey!

317
00:23:57,920 --> 00:23:58,960
Hey!

318
00:24:03,400 --> 00:24:05,240
I want to talk to you.

319
00:24:09,840 --> 00:24:12,240
I heard that

320
00:24:12,320 --> 00:24:14,800
there are special services here.

321
00:24:15,840 --> 00:24:17,920
If I want to use them,

322
00:24:18,000 --> 00:24:18,840
what do I need to do?

323
00:24:23,480 --> 00:24:24,840
My place

324
00:24:24,920 --> 00:24:27,640
doesn't offer any special services
beyond what's listed on the website.

325
00:24:28,160 --> 00:24:31,320
All guests here
can enjoy the same services equally.

326
00:24:32,880 --> 00:24:33,880
Enjoy your stay.

327
00:24:41,000 --> 00:24:42,320
Send someone to tail him.

328
00:24:43,040 --> 00:24:45,400
Dig into his background
and report back to me immediately.

329
00:24:45,920 --> 00:24:46,800
Yes, sir.

330
00:24:52,080 --> 00:24:53,880
Prepare a suite.

331
00:24:57,040 --> 00:24:58,520
The bait's taken.

332
00:25:00,920 --> 00:25:02,160
Don't worry.

333
00:25:02,680 --> 00:25:04,560
My team is good.

334
00:25:04,640 --> 00:25:05,920
I trained them myself.

335
00:25:06,000 --> 00:25:06,840
Right?

336
00:25:07,480 --> 00:25:08,520
Did you ever train me?

337
00:25:12,040 --> 00:25:12,880
Remember what I taught?

338
00:25:14,840 --> 00:25:15,960
Fine, you taught me.

339
00:25:23,800 --> 00:25:24,840
Are you scared?

340
00:25:29,240 --> 00:25:30,560
You have no idea

341
00:25:31,280 --> 00:25:34,280
how twisted Natee Suriyont really is

342
00:25:34,360 --> 00:25:35,960
behind that polished elite mask.

343
00:25:37,120 --> 00:25:38,280
I understand.

344
00:25:39,800 --> 00:25:40,800
Women

345
00:25:41,320 --> 00:25:43,280
are the most beautiful thing
in this world.

346
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:46,920
Anyone who can hurt women
is not a good person.

347
00:25:49,360 --> 00:25:51,760
This is our last chance.

348
00:25:53,080 --> 00:25:54,600
If you fail,

349
00:25:55,440 --> 00:25:59,040
Napa's sister's life will be in danger.

350
00:26:00,440 --> 00:26:03,880
No matter what I say,
I probably can't put your mind at ease.

351
00:26:18,280 --> 00:26:22,280
This sacred amulet has kept me safe,
protected me,

352
00:26:22,800 --> 00:26:24,320
and brought me victory in every battle.

353
00:26:25,960 --> 00:26:27,280
May I?

354
00:26:55,840 --> 00:26:57,040
I promise you.

355
00:26:57,120 --> 00:26:59,680
I will save Ms. Napa's sister.

356
00:27:00,200 --> 00:27:03,240
And I will destroy
Natee's entire criminal network.

357
00:27:04,400 --> 00:27:07,840
I won't allow him
to hurt anyone ever again.

358
00:27:16,800 --> 00:27:17,800
Sir.

359
00:27:25,120 --> 00:27:26,960
There's nothing suspicious.

360
00:27:28,600 --> 00:27:30,760
He's a newly rich rising tycoon,

361
00:27:30,840 --> 00:27:33,280
owner of a solar energy business
from Dubai.

362
00:27:34,520 --> 00:27:38,000
He just closed
a 40 million dollar deal in Malaysia.

363
00:27:38,080 --> 00:27:40,560
Hey, he looks legit.

364
00:27:41,080 --> 00:27:42,400
That's serious money.

365
00:27:42,920 --> 00:27:43,880
But sir,

366
00:27:44,800 --> 00:27:47,640
for VVIPs to enter
the exclusive clubhouse,

367
00:27:47,720 --> 00:27:49,480
Mr. Tiangmon has to approve it first.

368
00:27:49,560 --> 00:27:51,200
What makes him better than me?

369
00:27:51,920 --> 00:27:52,800
Answer me.

370
00:27:53,520 --> 00:27:56,200
He's just an old fart
who loves the sound of his own voice.

371
00:27:56,720 --> 00:27:59,040
He should already be retired,
and let someone like me

372
00:27:59,120 --> 00:28:00,880
be the boss's right-hand man.

373
00:28:03,080 --> 00:28:04,000
Yes, sir.

374
00:28:18,920 --> 00:28:22,560
Isn't the mountain scenery
around my resort appealing?

375
00:28:22,640 --> 00:28:24,040
Why are you cooped up in here?

376
00:28:30,000 --> 00:28:32,640
<i>Shan bu zhuan, lu zhuan.</i>

377
00:28:33,240 --> 00:28:36,240
The mountain doesn't move,
but the path always turns.

378
00:28:37,240 --> 00:28:39,560
Nature never stands still.

379
00:28:39,640 --> 00:28:41,720
Only people cling and remain rigid.

380
00:28:43,440 --> 00:28:44,760
You speak Chinese too.

381
00:28:46,960 --> 00:28:49,960
Well, lately he's been obsessed
with Chinese dramas.

382
00:28:51,480 --> 00:28:53,200
Chinese series are trending right now.

383
00:28:53,280 --> 00:28:56,160
I guess I'll have to watch some too.

384
00:28:56,920 --> 00:28:59,760
But the reason I came today was to ask you

385
00:28:59,840 --> 00:29:02,680
whether you're still interested
in upgrading to a premium membership.

386
00:29:03,200 --> 00:29:04,200
There's still time.

387
00:29:05,040 --> 00:29:06,560
But you told me earlier

388
00:29:07,080 --> 00:29:09,640
that there were no special services here.

389
00:29:09,720 --> 00:29:12,320
Well, here's the thing.
For the privacy of my members,

390
00:29:12,400 --> 00:29:14,600
I need to scan everyone's background

391
00:29:14,680 --> 00:29:15,520
before approving access.

392
00:29:17,080 --> 00:29:19,000
Hearing that, wow,

393
00:29:19,080 --> 00:29:21,080
I'm very excited.

394
00:29:23,240 --> 00:29:26,880
In that case, how much
is the membership? Just name the price.

395
00:29:27,880 --> 00:29:30,680
If your goods are really
as good as you claim,

396
00:29:30,760 --> 00:29:31,800
I'll go all in.

397
00:29:45,960 --> 00:29:47,160
Jack.

398
00:29:49,560 --> 00:29:50,840
<i>An accident, you say?</i>

399
00:29:50,920 --> 00:29:52,280
LUNG CANCER

400
00:29:52,360 --> 00:29:55,760
According to the foundation's report,
that's what they stated.

401
00:29:55,840 --> 00:29:57,600
Have you checked the CCTV?

402
00:29:58,120 --> 00:29:59,200
Yes.

403
00:29:59,720 --> 00:30:02,240
All the cameras…

404
00:30:02,320 --> 00:30:04,160
What? Were they broken?

405
00:30:04,240 --> 00:30:05,160
Yes.

406
00:30:07,800 --> 00:30:09,400
Jack was taken out

407
00:30:09,920 --> 00:30:11,720
because he knew who did it.

408
00:30:12,400 --> 00:30:13,960
We're not dealing with ordinary people.

409
00:30:19,640 --> 00:30:22,280
This has reached the boss.
Handle this immediately.

410
00:30:27,600 --> 00:30:30,120
THAI PM INVITED TO MEET XI JIN PING

411
00:30:30,720 --> 00:30:31,600
Sarge?

412
00:30:32,440 --> 00:30:33,320
Sarge, come here…

413
00:30:39,320 --> 00:30:41,440
Why are you here?
Do you want to get caught?

414
00:30:41,520 --> 00:30:44,600
Hey, I was worried about you.

415
00:30:44,680 --> 00:30:47,240
If Tiangmon starts suspecting you,
how am I supposed to help?

416
00:30:48,240 --> 00:30:49,360
I can survive on my own.

417
00:30:50,440 --> 00:30:53,480
Survive in a way that made me
clean up after you twice already?

418
00:30:55,120 --> 00:30:57,080
We're on the same team.
Isn't that your job?

419
00:30:57,160 --> 00:31:00,240
Oh wow, now we're a team?

420
00:31:00,320 --> 00:31:01,920
Back then, you pushed us aside,

421
00:31:02,000 --> 00:31:04,200
said we were useless,
we weren't fit for this mission.

422
00:31:04,280 --> 00:31:06,480
Don't do anything reckless.
What if the plan fails?

423
00:31:10,040 --> 00:31:12,160
I don't have time to argue with you.

424
00:31:12,680 --> 00:31:16,480
Even though we dealt with Jack,
if this reaches Phoenix so quickly,

425
00:31:17,840 --> 00:31:20,000
we may be facing dangers
we didn't anticipate.

426
00:31:39,080 --> 00:31:40,080
Yes, Boss.

427
00:31:40,800 --> 00:31:42,480
I was just about to call you.

428
00:31:43,080 --> 00:31:45,080
The agent you ordered me to handle

429
00:31:45,600 --> 00:31:46,600
is dead.

430
00:31:50,240 --> 00:31:53,040
For their network to spread this far,

431
00:31:53,760 --> 00:31:55,680
with gunmen and assassins,

432
00:31:56,200 --> 00:31:57,720
there must be an entire army behind it.

433
00:31:59,000 --> 00:32:00,680
You mean

434
00:32:01,360 --> 00:32:04,360
besides Jack,
there are other dangerous people too?

435
00:32:07,640 --> 00:32:10,000
But if our teamwork is this solid,

436
00:32:10,080 --> 00:32:12,720
they can spread their wings
and bring in an army, assassins,

437
00:32:12,800 --> 00:32:15,280
or even John Wick all they want.
I’d knock them senseless.

438
00:32:19,440 --> 00:32:20,760
Someone like you?

439
00:32:27,640 --> 00:32:28,960
Someone like who?

440
00:32:30,040 --> 00:32:31,720
If you want to talk about good teamwork,

441
00:32:32,240 --> 00:32:35,160
then first prove you can take down
their human-trafficking network

442
00:32:35,240 --> 00:32:38,840
properly, without any mess afterward.

443
00:32:39,440 --> 00:32:41,200
It'll be proper for sure.

444
00:32:42,240 --> 00:32:44,360
I'd stake my he…

445
00:32:47,760 --> 00:32:49,880
I'd stake my heart on it.

446
00:32:56,840 --> 00:32:58,040
My boss's calling.

447
00:32:58,120 --> 00:33:00,320
What are you waiting for?
Don't ruin our plan.

448
00:33:06,560 --> 00:33:09,120
There's an order to heighten security,

449
00:33:09,640 --> 00:33:11,920
especially for Natee's auction tonight.

450
00:33:12,760 --> 00:33:16,600
They might choose that place
as their next target.

451
00:33:23,640 --> 00:33:24,840
Abort the mission…

452
00:33:24,920 --> 00:33:26,160
What? Abort the mission?

453
00:33:26,240 --> 00:33:27,840
- What?
- Abort the mission…

454
00:33:27,920 --> 00:33:29,000
It can't be aborted…

455
00:33:39,640 --> 00:33:42,800
Vitamin C helps strengthen your body.

456
00:33:42,880 --> 00:33:46,160
Have a lot of these, okay, Mr. Dan?
You'll be discharged sooner.

457
00:33:47,440 --> 00:33:49,400
Then I won't take it.

458
00:33:50,200 --> 00:33:52,000
I want to stay here longer.

459
00:33:52,840 --> 00:33:55,760
If I go home, I'll be all alone.

460
00:33:56,840 --> 00:33:58,520
And I still haven't found my cat.

461
00:34:00,040 --> 00:34:01,960
Don't cry.

462
00:34:02,040 --> 00:34:03,800
Eat some oranges. I'll peel them for you.

463
00:34:04,800 --> 00:34:06,160
- Uh.
- Oh?

464
00:34:06,240 --> 00:34:09,320
- Come here. Let me take a look.
- It burns.

465
00:34:10,199 --> 00:34:11,080
Let me see.

466
00:34:43,960 --> 00:34:45,199
Dan, how are you doing?

467
00:34:45,280 --> 00:34:47,360
Hey, whoa.

468
00:34:47,440 --> 00:34:49,080
Sarge, how'd you get here?

469
00:34:50,600 --> 00:34:51,639
Sarge?

470
00:34:57,240 --> 00:34:58,400
Not Sarge.

471
00:34:58,480 --> 00:35:00,480
Not Sarge.

472
00:35:00,560 --> 00:35:03,160
Serge. His name is Serge.

473
00:35:03,240 --> 00:35:04,840
Serge. Serge.

474
00:35:04,920 --> 00:35:06,000
- Serge?
- Yes.

475
00:35:06,080 --> 00:35:07,960
- Yes, Serge. I am…
- Serge.

476
00:35:08,040 --> 00:35:10,240
- Serge.
- It's Serge. My full name is…

477
00:35:10,760 --> 00:35:12,440
Sergio. I'm Dan's older brother.

478
00:35:12,520 --> 00:35:14,160
- Yes.
- I just knew my bro got hit by a car,

479
00:35:14,240 --> 00:35:15,480
- so I rushed over.
- Thank you.

480
00:35:15,560 --> 00:35:16,760
- You're his brother?
- Yes.

481
00:35:16,840 --> 00:35:20,040
But you said you live alone with a cat.

482
00:35:26,080 --> 00:35:27,680
- Ah.
- Yeah.

483
00:35:27,760 --> 00:35:30,080
Yeah, Dan lives alone with a cat.

484
00:35:30,160 --> 00:35:31,600
I live alone with a dog.

485
00:35:31,680 --> 00:35:34,960
Dan lives with a cat in Pha Mok.
I live alone with a dog in Bangkok.

486
00:35:35,040 --> 00:35:37,440
- In Bangkok.
- Yes, in Bangkok.

487
00:35:37,520 --> 00:35:39,800
Then I'll let the siblings
stay together for now.

488
00:35:39,880 --> 00:35:40,720
- All right.
- Excuse me.

489
00:35:40,800 --> 00:35:42,280
- Okay.
- Okay.

490
00:35:43,600 --> 00:35:45,960
- Come again. We'll just talk a bit.
- Mm, okay.

491
00:35:51,480 --> 00:35:52,520
She's pretty.

492
00:35:53,680 --> 00:35:55,160
What the hell are you doing?

493
00:36:03,360 --> 00:36:04,360
All set.

494
00:36:04,880 --> 00:36:07,080
I transferred fake crypto
into their account system.

495
00:36:07,160 --> 00:36:09,360
That's slick. How'd you do it?

496
00:36:10,080 --> 00:36:12,720
I just created another dummy account.

497
00:36:12,800 --> 00:36:16,240
Then I funneled fake crypto
into the system through a node.

498
00:36:16,320 --> 00:36:19,720
The system shows the numbers rising
in real time, one million dollars.

499
00:36:21,440 --> 00:36:24,240
- Won't they check?
- Yeah, they'll check.

500
00:36:24,760 --> 00:36:27,720
Normally,
the system audits five layers back.

501
00:36:28,240 --> 00:36:31,760
All I need right now is to make it
look real enough for Natee to bite.

502
00:36:31,840 --> 00:36:33,600
By the time he realizes it's fake,

503
00:36:34,120 --> 00:36:35,960
- our mission will already be done.
- Hey.

504
00:36:36,480 --> 00:36:38,200
You're pretty damn good.

505
00:36:38,280 --> 00:36:39,440
I'm the real deal.

506
00:36:39,520 --> 00:36:41,200
This job's easy.

507
00:36:41,280 --> 00:36:43,000
- You noobs.
- Easy my ass.

508
00:36:44,000 --> 00:36:45,000
We're screwed.

509
00:36:46,680 --> 00:36:47,920
Sorry, bro.

510
00:36:48,520 --> 00:36:49,760
Secrets are out.

511
00:36:51,360 --> 00:36:53,920
He met a woman and spilled everything.

512
00:36:54,000 --> 00:36:55,880
Women are the reason we'll fail.

513
00:36:55,960 --> 00:36:57,400
Why are you blaming women?

514
00:36:57,920 --> 00:37:00,040
It was just me and Kla, right?

515
00:37:00,120 --> 00:37:01,840
Can you stop trying to look cool?

516
00:37:01,920 --> 00:37:05,640
One mistake from you means all our lives.

517
00:37:06,160 --> 00:37:10,040
Sarge, but if we didn't get info and help
from Ms. Napa and Ms. Khim,

518
00:37:10,120 --> 00:37:11,920
we wouldn't be here.

519
00:37:12,000 --> 00:37:14,600
Do you know Ms. Duangnet
has ordered the mission aborted?

520
00:37:14,680 --> 00:37:16,280
It can't be aborted.

521
00:37:16,360 --> 00:37:18,760
My sister and the women who were captured

522
00:37:18,840 --> 00:37:20,760
are waiting to be saved.

523
00:37:20,840 --> 00:37:24,200
Mr. Kla, you promised us.
This is our last chance.

524
00:37:25,760 --> 00:37:27,600
Sarge, I'm begging you.

525
00:37:28,200 --> 00:37:29,960
If I wanted fame,

526
00:37:30,040 --> 00:37:31,520
I wouldn't take this mission.

527
00:37:38,760 --> 00:37:39,800
Miss,

528
00:37:40,880 --> 00:37:43,880
tell us what crimes has Natee committed?

529
00:37:58,720 --> 00:37:59,720
Hey, open the door.

530
00:38:06,960 --> 00:38:07,840
Back off.

531
00:38:10,160 --> 00:38:11,400
Hey, hey, don't.

532
00:38:11,480 --> 00:38:13,080
No! Don't.

533
00:38:20,120 --> 00:38:20,960
Come here.

534
00:38:24,720 --> 00:38:25,880
Okay, roger that.

535
00:38:29,880 --> 00:38:32,880
Man, I really want
something cold to drink.

536
00:38:34,400 --> 00:38:37,400
Excuse me, do you have something like…

537
00:38:38,400 --> 00:38:41,280
Something that hits the throat?

538
00:38:41,360 --> 00:38:43,040
What do you mean? Hits the throat?

539
00:38:43,120 --> 00:38:44,720
Like… Something that…

540
00:38:46,040 --> 00:38:47,720
- What are you doing?
- You guys are next.

541
00:39:15,040 --> 00:39:16,680
<i>This is our first item.</i>

542
00:39:17,280 --> 00:39:19,720
<i>Fresh internal organs, guaranteed.</i>

543
00:39:19,800 --> 00:39:20,880
Please begin bidding.

544
00:39:21,400 --> 00:39:22,680
- Hey!
- Run!

545
00:39:24,600 --> 00:39:26,280
I'm here!

546
00:39:45,800 --> 00:39:47,520
So this is how you want to play it?

547
00:39:49,320 --> 00:39:51,040
You're lucky.

548
00:39:51,120 --> 00:39:52,640
You get to see my trick shot.

549
00:39:55,720 --> 00:39:57,960
Meet Dab the Red Inferno!

550
00:40:23,200 --> 00:40:26,440
Then, do you mind if I ask your name?

551
00:40:26,520 --> 00:40:27,440
It's all right.

552
00:40:28,160 --> 00:40:29,360
My name is…

553
00:40:31,720 --> 00:40:32,680
Mook.

554
00:40:33,200 --> 00:40:36,200
And then the car hit me, boom!
That's how I ended up like this.

555
00:40:36,280 --> 00:40:38,040
It's… It's like…

556
00:40:38,120 --> 00:40:39,680
- This is his head, right?
- Yes.

557
00:40:39,760 --> 00:40:42,320
Here. Try hitting it,
and use this to help. See?

558
00:40:42,400 --> 00:40:44,080
- Yeah.
- Use my own hand to push it down?

559
00:40:50,520 --> 00:40:53,560
You know "In-car"?
The back seat's this wide,

560
00:40:53,640 --> 00:40:54,840
real comfy.

561
00:41:03,040 --> 00:41:07,200
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
